                          "name": "q5a",
                          "fill": "#64748B",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "No.JS uses JavaScript Proxy objects to create reactive state. When you declare state with the :state directive, changes automatically propagate to all bound elements in the DOM — no manual updates, no setState calls, no re-renders needed.",
